definition: Yicheng county in Linfen 臨汾|临汾[Lin2 fen2], Shanxi
surname Yi/alternative name for 絳|绛[Jiang4] capital of the Jin State during the Spring and Autumn Period (770-475 BC)
wing/area surrounding the bullseye of a target/to assist/one of the 28 constellations of Chinese astronomy/old variant of 翌

sentences.english: Wang Jiwen was born in Xin'zhuang Village, Jicheng, Shanxi province in 1934.
sentences.chinese: 王吉文，1934年出生于山西省翼城縣辛莊村。

sentences.english: Yicheng, it said, had been trying a two-child policy for 25 years.
sentences.chinese: 翼城縣據說已經施行“二胎”政策25年了。
